author: Russell Brand
description:
Elon Musk nukes his alliance with Trump by tweeting that Trump is “in the Epstein files”—before quickly deleting the post. In this explosive episode, Russell explores the deeper meaning behind the Musk–Trump split: the crisis in MAGA, the rise of tech feudalism, and the future of populism. With JD Vance defending Trump, Rogan stunned, and Twitter/X turning into a battleground of billionaires and burnouts, what does this rupture reveal about America’s next political transformation? Is this just personal ego—or the beginning of something much bigger?
